From: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>
Subject: [PATCH] backend-vnc: skip getpwnam guard in vnc_handle_auth

Bridgething's dev image runs weston-vnc with
--disable-transport-layer-security and a pam_permit
/etc/pam.d/weston-remote-access service so VNC is a zero-friction debug
surface on the private USB-CDC gadget link between device and dev host.

Upstream's vnc_handle_auth precondition - that the VNC username map to
a real local account whose uid matches weston's process uid - forces
every connect to type "root" before pam_permit gets to wave the
credentials through. That adds friction without security benefit on a
single-account dev image whose only network reachability is the host
USB cable.

Skip the getpwnam check and let PAM make the decision unconditionally.
On prod images this code path is unreachable because vnc-backend.so
isn't packaged.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [downstream policy]
Signed-off-by: Joey Eamigh <55670930+JoeyEamigh@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 libweston/backend-vnc/vnc.c | 7 -------
 1 file changed, 7 deletions(-)

diff --git a/libweston/backend-vnc/vnc.c b/libweston/backend-vnc/vnc.c
--- a/libweston/backend-vnc/vnc.c
+++ b/libweston/backend-vnc/vnc.c
@@ -485,13 +485,6 @@ vnc_pointer_event(struct nvnc_client *client, uint16_t x, uint16_t y,
 static bool
 vnc_handle_auth(const char *username, const char *password, void *userdata)
 {
-	struct passwd *pw = getpwnam(username);
-
-	if (!pw || pw->pw_uid != getuid()) {
-		weston_log("VNC: wrong user '%s'\n", username);
-		return false;
-	}
-
 	return weston_authenticate_user(username, password);
 }

